dashboard.definition:
{
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem statement\n\nSearching for IP addresses in Splunk is super expensive due to how the indexing process works. Specifically when a user searches for `index=something dest=10.20.30.1` the platform generates a LISPY `[ AND 1 10 20 30 index::something ]` which matches any event containing `1`, `10`, `20`, `30` and then relies on schema on the fly to sure they are in sequence and in the right order. This elimination after schema on the fly is very wasteful and early elimination at the lexicon stage would return huge dividends.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nWe use REGEX to extract things that appear to be ip address and write them into an indexed field. We can then modify our searches to use that indexed field for accelaration.\n\nFor example we take our search `index=something 10.20.30.1` and add the reference to the indexed field `index=something ip::10.20.30.1 dest=10.20.30.1`. This changes the LISPY so that it includes the indexed field `[ AND 1 10 20 30 index::something ip::10.20.30.1 ]` which then eliminates events that contain `1`, `10`, `20`, `30` but are not IP addresses, for example `1/30/20 value=10` saving the extraction and parsing of a large number of events.\n\n### Sample data\n\nThis application creates a log file for us to test and apply the method to. We include obvious invalid IP addresses so that we can try to exclude them.\n\n#### `may_contain_ips`\n\n    05-01-2021 13:28:25 dest=166.138.75.176.208.89 130.237.248.205 259.225.273.220 dest=253.248.199.201\n    05-01-2021 13:28:28 dest=21.162.239.136\n    05-01-2021 13:28:32 ip=166.244.219.272 dest=140.219.264.132 http://120.240.249.253 dest=237.166.265.220\n    05-01-2021 13:28:50 http://130.134.137.208 dest=210.193.249.255 68.160.245.176 http://209.230.87.220\n    05-01-2021 13:29:21 dest=249.173.68.216 dest=189.218.100.173\n    05-01-2021 13:29:26 ip=160.209.136.145 http://149.128.151.220 http://222.275.97.164 237.133.70.70\n    05-01-2021 13:30:22 dest=176.258.189 ip=254.187.179.224 ip=282.169.196.97\n    05-01-2021 13:30:31 dest=119.256.131.127\n    05-01-2021 13:30:34 102.135.145.44 http://228.283.253.223\n    05-01-2021 13:31:17 ip=234.239.274.174 dest=259.54.244.177 162.233.252.253 dest=62.223.206.202\n    05-01-2021 13:31:40 78.270.257.241 170.252.235.57.171\n    05-01-2021 13:31:49 258.233.25.170 134.106.222.252 ip=56.101.122.201 http://234.206.197.58\n    05-01-2021 13:32:10 http://154.197.182.183 ip=146.279.182.192 dest=219.167.258.212 242.235.130.83\n\nNote that from the above we have some invalid ip addresses, examples:\n\n* `282.169.196.97` the first octet is greater than 254\n* `166.138.75.176.208.89` is too long\n\nTo reject these we need to fine tune the regular expressions to exclude them. The following configuration only matches a single sourcetype, but it could be applied to all events\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_conf_props": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### props.conf\n\nFrom `default/props.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n[find_ip_addresses]\nTIME_FORMAT = %d-%m-%Y %H:%M:%S\nSHOULD_LINEMERGE=false\nLINE_BREAKER=([\\n\\r]+)\nTRANSFORMS-find-find_ip_addresses=find_ip_addresses\n```\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_conf_transforms": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### transforms.conf\n\nFrom `default/transforms.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n[find_ip_addresses]\nREGEX = (?<![\\d\\.])((?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9][0-9]?)\\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9][0-9]?))(?![\\d\\.])\nSOURCE_KEY = _raw\nREPEAT_MATCH=true\nFORMAT = ip::\"$1\"\nWRITE_META = true\n```\n"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {
						"latest": "$global_time.latest$",
						"earliest": "$global_time.earliest$"
					}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {
						"latest": "$global_time.latest$",
						"earliest": "$global_time.earliest$"
					}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"inputs": {},
	"layout": {
		"options": {},
		"globalInputs": [],
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"layoutId": "layout_1",
					"label": "New tab"
				}
			]
		},
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 1440,
							"h": 703
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_props",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 703,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_transforms",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 703,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					}
				],
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 960
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"description": "",
	"title": "Find IP addresses"
}
